<subSubSection lastPageId="101" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,798,735,802]" box="[151,307,776,802]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<figureCitation box="[151,307,776,802]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154–158</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1436,856,2002]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol" authorityName="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol" box="[460,932,856,882]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baubo">
<emphasis box="[460,571,856,881]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">H. baubo</emphasis>
Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1116,856,882]" name="Thailand" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, especially in the shape of segments IX and X. 
<taxonomicName authority="Oláh &amp; Johanson, 2008" authorityName="Oláh &amp; Johanson" authorityYear="2008" box="[397,663,896,921]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khasigiri" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[397,663,896,921]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Hydropsyche khasigiri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[679,821,896,922]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is unique in having shallow and narrower intersegmental depression; the apicoventral setose processes are shorter and not tapering; the harpagones are broadening apicad, not narrowing as in 
<taxonomicName box="[543,655,976,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baubo">
<emphasis box="[543,655,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">H. baubo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and the sclerous endothecal process is bifid, and armed with a shorter dorsobasal arm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1436,856,2002]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Male. Large, body and wings brown with light pubescence. Forewing membrane uniformly brown without pattern. Maxillary palp formula I-II-(III, IV)-V, segment V as long as segments I–IV together. Head dorsum dark brown, with 9 dark brown setal warts. Swollen setal wart present on proepisternum. Each pretarsal claws asymmetrical, laterally flanked by setal bundle. Spur formula 244. Both protibia with posteroapical spur smaller than anteroapical spur.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1436,856,2002]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Wings. Venation typical for the genus. Forewing crossveins m-cu and cu separate. Sc and R, and Cu2 and A running separate before costa. Hind wing Sc and R meeting before costa at crossvein r. Stem of M and Cu1 running closely. Median cell closed. Fork 1 present. Forewing length 11.0 mm, hind wing length 7.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1436,856,2002]" lastBlockId="101.[151,1436,152,578]" lastPageId="101" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
Male genitalia. Abdominal segment IX fused annularly. Median keel long, gradually narrowing, sharply triangular, almost tapering in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[656,760,1416,1442]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface granulose; lateral surfaces flat, glabrous; anterior margin arciform; ventrum short; dorsum 2 times longer than ventrum (
<figureCitation box="[1124,1232,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
). Antecosta well developed into double line; narrowing dorsally before margin; with external groove of antecostal suture. Apical lobe on posterolateral margins broad, triangular (
<figureCitation box="[794,901,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
). Posterior spine row intermittent with long break at segment X (
<figureCitation box="[400,504,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
); with 3–4 setae immediately below median keel and on apical lobes. Depression between segments IX and X shallow, short. Body of segment X basally short in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1422,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
); basally long, nearly triangular in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[710,815,1656,1682]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
); rounded quadrangular in dorsal view; constricting slightly basad. Lateral setose areas (preanal appendages) present centrally and distally, forming anterior, well delineated, pale patch and more diffused, loosely packed, groups of setae on distal margin. Apicoventral setose lobes modified into pair of short, digitiform processes with setae restricted to apex; very short, not narrowing apically (
<figureCitation box="[352,455,1816,1842]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
). Dorsal interlobular gap narrow, deep (
<figureCitation box="[927,1030,1816,1842]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
). Apicodorsal setose lobe forming anterior setose ridge, or crest; shallow, smooth cavity on segment X present; short, wide, darkly pigmented transverse suture running ventrally on each side from bottom of intersegmental depression (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1334,1896,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view visible as prominent suture crossing middle of segment X (
<figureCitation box="[974,1080,1936,1962]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
). Longitudinal suture running anteriorly of lateral setose area. Coxopodites slightly exceeding apex of segment X; each with dorsal margin with basal half slightly sinuous; dilating distally from mid-length; nearly straight in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1423,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
). Harpagones curving dorsomesad (
<figureCitation box="[560,728,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 154, 156</figureCitation>
); nearly parallel sided. Phallic apparatus simply bent (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 157</figureCitation>
); flat due to shortened, ventrad curving basal section; broadening only along ventrad curving part. Phallotheca with straight dorsal margin, except curving dorsad immediately before apex. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Zang &amp; R.H. Petersen" authorityYear="1989" box="[1153,1299,272,298]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phallaceae" genus="Endophallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Phallales" pageId="101" pageNumber="9" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Endophallus</taxonomicName>
attached to dorsal wall of phallotheca, reaching over to phallic apparatus bend. Phallotremal sclerites falciform, broad. Pair of bifid, sclerous endothecal processes, armed with short, dorsobasal arm (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1219,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 157</figureCitation>
). Sclerous ventral process of phallotheca much shorter than phallotremal sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[909,1011,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 154–158" captionStartId="101.[151,269,1609,1633]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,627,1561]" captionTargetId="figure-195@101.[151,1436,589,1601]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURES 154–158. Hydropsyche khasigiri Oláh &amp; Barnard, new species, holotype, male. 154 — genitalia, lateral; 155 — genitalia, dorsal; 156 — gonocoxite, ventral; 157 — phallus, lateral; 158 — phallus apex, ventral." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 158</figureCitation>
); in ventral view with rounded bifid apical margin.
</paragraph>
